The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically the problem of deleting vertices to obtain a graph embeddable on a surface of a given Euler genus. This problem is related to graph theory, computational geometry, and combinatorics, which are all covered by the above sub-categories. The paper also mentions previous algorithms for the surface being a sphere, which suggests that the authors are building upon existing research in computational complexity and graph algorithms, which are covered by cs.CC and cs.DS.
